</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53A8B38AFB0A6672FF77AD98FC1EBEEF" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="1B0DE001FB0A6672FF77AD98FD19BE84" blockId="14.[151,1436,152,551]" box="[198,740,413,439]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="29C63C13FB0A6672FF77AD98FECEBE84" bold="true" box="[198,307,413,439]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ecology:</emphasis>
has been found at 
<quantity id="DC4A4DE4FB0A6672FDBEAD98FD69BE84" box="[527,660,413,439]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.625" metricValueMax="15.05" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="m" value="762.5" valueMax="1505.0" valueMin="20.0">20–1505 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B0DE001FB0A6672FF77ADC7FC1EBEEF" blockId="14.[151,1436,152,551]" box="[198,995,450,476]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The name 
<taxonomicName id="DCB29B82FB0A6672FEF3ADC7FE3CBEE8" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1883" box="[322,449,450,475]" class="Malacostraca" family="Stenothoidae" genus="Metopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptocarpa">
<emphasis id="29C63C13FB0A6672FEF3ADC7FE3CBEE8" box="[322,449,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">leptocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the very long carpus on gnathopod 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53A8B38AFB0A6672FF77ADE2FBBFBD14" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1B0DE001FB0A6672FF77ADE2FBBFBD14" blockId="14.[151,1436,152,551]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="29C63C13FB0A6672FF77ADE2FEC2BD32" bold="true" box="[198,319,487,513]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very easily distinguishable from other 
<taxonomicName id="DCB29B82FB0A6672FC7FADEDFBDABD32" authorityName="Boeck" authorityYear="1871" box="[974,1063,488,513]" class="Malacostraca" family="Stenothoidae" genus="Metopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="29C63C13FB0A6672FC7FADEDFBDABD32" box="[974,1063,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Metopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the very elongate carpus of gnathopod 1, and to some degree also by the long peduncles of uropods 1 and 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
